> This ballpark classic is perfect for baseball season! All the components cook in
> the oven on a baking sheet, leaving you with almost no cleanup. That way,
> you'll be able to sit back and enjoy the game!

== Roast the Veggies and Sausages ==

Prep the veggies: Wash and dry all produce. Preheat the #oven{} to 425 degrees.
Core, seed, and thinly slice the @Green Bell Pepper{2} and @Red Bell Pepper{2}.
Halve, peel, and thinly slice the @Yellow Onion{2}(thinly sliced).

Toss the peppers and onions on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of
@Olive Oil{1%tablespoon} and season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}. Poke a few holes
in the @Sweet Italian Pork Sausage{18%ounce} with a #fork{} and place on top of
the vegetables. Place in the oven for ~{15%minutes}.

Prep the remaining ingredients: Meanwhile, split the @Po'boy Rolls{4} (but don't
cut all the way through). Trim and discard the bottom inch from the
@Asparagus{12%ounce}, then halve the asparagus lengthwise.

== Broil the Asparagus ==

After 15 minutes of roasting, remove the baking sheet from the oven. Set the
#broiler{} to high or heat the oven to 500 degrees. Add the asparagus to one
side of the baking sheet and toss with a large drizzle of
@Olive Oil{1%tablespoon}, the @Italian Seasoning{2%teaspoon}, and a pinch of
@Salt{} and @Pepper{}. Return the baking sheet to the oven for ~{4-6%minutes},
until the veggies are slightly charred and the sausage is cooked through.

== Toast the Rolls ==

Place the rolls on the empty #baking sheets{} and toast in the oven for
~{2-3%minutes}. While the rolls toast, cut the sausages into ½-inch slices on
a diagonal.

== Assemble ==

Top each toasted roll with the @Italian Cheese Blend{1%cup}, peppers, onions,
and sausage. Serve with the broiled asparagus and enjoy!

> TIP: If you have extra sandwich fillings, simply serve them to the side!